3) Shared Scoreboard (client + server forwarding)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Files:
- client/src/components/common-components/Scoreboard.js
- client/src/components/common-components/GameTicTacToe.js
- client/src/components/common-components/GameRPS.js
- client/src/components/common-components/GameChess.js
- client/src/components/common-components/GameTruthOrDare.js
- client/src/components/VideoChat.js
- server/server.js

What was done:
- Added a reusable `Scoreboard` component.
- Wired all games to emit `gameScore` to the partner and call `updateScore(...)` locally at win/point events.
- Added server forwarding for `gameScore`.
- Implemented scoreboard rendering during gameplay (in VideoChat) and reset on partner disconnect / skip.

Score-counting bug fix:
- Fixed scoreboard “jumping to 3” by:
  - Adding per-game `useRef` guards to ensure updateScore fires only once per round:
    - GameTicTacToe, GameRPS, GameChess, GameTruthOrDare
  - Adding a 1-second debounce safety net in the parent `updateScore` implementation.
  - Routing incoming `gameScore` through the same debounced `updateScore` and cleaning up the socket handler.

Outcome:
- Each win increments by exactly +1.

